\begin_layout Section
Traversability Definitions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Traversability is defined as the ability of a robot or autonomous vehicle to navigate across or through a section of given environment without sustaining damage [14].
 The probabilistic risk model presented in this work is a sum of all environmental hazards that would effect the risk of a robot successfully traversing the environment.
 Each hazard is given a term in the summation and is defined as a traversability metric.
\end_layout

